How to Stop Mozilla Firefox From Consuming CPU Cycles?

00:00:11.166 --> 00:00:16.632
Open Firefox Browser on your computer.

00:00:16.633 --> 00:00:25.166
Type about:config in the address bar.

00:00:25.166 --> 00:00:34.632
Read the statement and click 'I'll be careful, I promise!' button.

00:00:34.633 --> 00:00:56.066
Type "browser.cache.disk.capacity" in the search bar.

00:00:56.066 --> 00:01:16.832
Double click on the line and then modify the value to 16384.

00:01:16.833 --> 00:01:25.433
 

00:01:25.433 --> 00:01:34.766
Now press Control, alt and delete key on your keyboard.

00:01:34.766 --> 00:02:00.066
 

00:02:00.066 --> 00:02:07.666
CPU Usage for Firefox should now stay nominally under 20%.

00:02:07.666 --> 00:02:11.666
 

00:02:11.666 --> 00:02:17.466
This is How you can stop firefox from consuming cpu cycles.

